Dawn probe snaps first close-up of giant asteroid
TheDawn space probe has returned the first up-close and detailed image of the astronomical asteroid Vesta, which it began orbiting over the weekend.
Vesta, which is 330 miles in diameter, is the second-most-massive object in the asteroid belt between Mars and Jupiter. Considered to be a protoplanet, it is thought to be the source of meteorites that fall to Earth.
NASA's news release and Space.com have more.
